H. No. 3103 / 57 OG No. 6, 1016 (February 6, 1961)

[ REPUBLIC ACT NO. 2790, June 19, 1960 ]

AN ACT CREATING CERTAIN BARRIOS IN THE MUNICIPALITY OF VIRAC, PROVINCE OF CATANDUANES.

Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the Philippines in Congress assembled:

SECTION 1. The following places in the Municipality of Virac, Province of Catanduanes, are declared as barrios of said municipality, to wit:

Pajo as Barrio Bagui, Pajo;

Bigaa as Barrio Bigaa;

Calampong as Barrio Calampong;

Buenavista as Barrio Buenavista;

Capilihan as Barrio Capilihan;

Dugui (TO-O) as Barrio Dugui (TO-O);

Hawan (Ilaya) as Barrio Hawan (Ilaya);

Igang as Barrio Igang;

Palta (Small) as Barrio Palta (Small);

Sto. Cristo (Cabijian) as Barrio Sto. Cristo (Cabijian) ;

San Isidro (Dugui Wala) as Barrio San Isidro (Dugui Wala);

San Vicente (Dugui Wala) as Barrio San Vicente (Dugui Wala);

San Isidro, Pajo, as Barrio San Isidro, Pajo; and

Valencia as Barrio Valencia.

SEC. 2. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.

Enacted without Executive approval, June 19, 1960.
